name: Siddarth Srinivas
text: #Karnan: The film on the whole is detailed and long drawn out, but keeps giving us exciting stretches that make us root for @dhanushkraja and all the other characters in the village. The start up, interval block and the climax are pitch perfect, to say the least!

name: Siddarth Srinivas
text: #Karnan: @mari_selvaraj is the man of the moment right now, the way he makes use of imagery, symbolism and tough themes in the society as his building blocks is superb to watch. The film's backbone is its realistic writing, with its unflinching and massy stretches balanced out!

name: Siddarth Srinivas
text: #Karnan: Tremendous. An authentic, affecting drama that brings about another tale on oppression in a dramatic, impactful manner. Fantastically shot, has an excellent score with @dhanushkraja delivering a ragemaxx performance. Take a bow, @mari_selvaraj üëè

name: Siddarth Srinivas
text: #Karnan Interval: Bloody good. Mari Selvaraj skilfully builds up an engrossing drama laden with emotional tension. @dhanushkraja in a fierce, firing role is setting up another long list of awards already, this is a spectacular film so far with lots of clap-worthy moments!

#KarnanPressMeet

'Independent cinema is not about going out and making films on our own. 

Independent cinema is when a man is able to tell his story without any restrictions, having a free flow of thoughts. 

#Karnan is an INDEPENDENT film' - @mari_selvaraj üëèüëå

text:

'Nalla vishayangal ipdi dhan takkunu nadakkum' - D üëçüëå

name: Siddarth Srinivas
text: #Drishyam2: Mohanlal as Georgekutty is a character one just cannot get enough of. With a majority of stares and restrained dialogue delivery, the veteran simply steals the show once again. The fantastic final 45 minute stretch is a treat for sure, good load of thrills!

name: Siddarth Srinivas
text: #Drishyam2: Brilliant! Mohanlal and Jeethu Joseph together deliver one of the best sequels ever made in Indian cinema, a film that answers all your questions in style. Doesn't have too many wow moments like the first, but is an intelligently written film that does surprise. Win!

text: #Eeswaran: Susienthiran has done just enough to package and pack up the film within a short span, keeping in mind the limitations he had during the pandemic. The story is as old as the hills but there are some fun moments thanks to @SilambarasanTR_ who is really good onscreen!

name: Siddarth Srinivas
text: #Master: Give it to @anirudhofficial for multiplying the intensity big time with his addictive score. He continues to deliver huge contributions to every film he steps into, some of his cues here are truly international. Andha phone ringtone, oru madhri mandaikulla odite iruku!

name: Siddarth Srinivas
text: #Master: Bhavani by @VijaySethuOffl - what a ferocious and ruthless baddie, will go down as one of the best villains in recent memory. VJS proves his versatility in this brilliantly sketched role that is the biggest win of the film, the duel with Vijay at the end is too good!

name: Siddarth Srinivas
text: #Master: A super stylish outing for #ThalapathyVijay, who gets it absolutely right with his swag, looks and his performance as well. Arguably his best makeover since Thuppakki, with loads to 'celebrate' for fans in full!

name: Siddarth Srinivas
text: #Master: Mighty. Easily the most unique Thalapathy Vijay film in the past few years, having its mass moments shining more than anything else. Lokesh proves how big an action veriyan he is, VJ and VJS battle it out in a fight fest where every stunt sequence is a treat to watch!

name: Siddarth Srinivas
text: #Master Interval: Very engaging. Both the Vijays in sublime form, lighting up the screen in a film supported by AMAZING cinematography and music. Slight dips here and there, but that doesn't matter in the bigger picture - Vaathi on song!

name: Siddarth Srinivas
text: Cheers to @Atlee_dir and @priyaatlee for presenting an important film like #Andhaghaaram, helping it get more eyeballs. After his numerous box office BBs, this is a different feather on producer #Atlee's cap - looking forward to more striking content hereon!

name: Siddarth Srinivas
text: @JAISURYAN Yes. Solid film. Have small issues with the climax but that's okay. This is one of the best debuts in a long time.

name: Siddarth Srinivas
text: #Andhaghaaram: Arguably, this is indeed a perfect film to land on a premium platform like Netflix. Top picture clarity, great sound & is trippy enough to suit the audience that will throng this base. The kind of content that OTT needs to fuel up more attention towards it.

name: Siddarth Srinivas
text: #Andhaghaaram: The fact that it makes such perfect use of its cast is another factor to go wow at. The strengths of @iam_arjundas, @vinoth_kishan and the rest have been identified well in advance and they bring in their best. Each and every character in the film makes a mark.

name: Siddarth Srinivas
text: #Andhaghaaram: There's a towering level of clarity with which @vvignarajan etches his storyline, as his pinpoint narration makes sure we don't skip a beat when everything comes together at the end. It's complex, yet clear and clever throughout, and that's its biggest success.

name: Siddarth Srinivas
text: #Andhaghaaram: Awesomeness. A splendidly crafted supernatural suspense thriller that sets up the stage in solid fashion and delivers a knockout punch. Give it your utmost concentration, and you'll be intrigued for the entire 3 hours. @vvignarajan is here to stay, solid debut!
